EAAlgorithm Internal Security
Handbook
Version 1.0
Confdential – Internal Use Only
1. Password & Authentication Requirements
Strong authentication practices are critical to preventing unauthorized access. EAAlgo-
rithm enforces strict password and identity management controls to reduce the risk of
compromise.
General Requirements
• Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) is mandatory for all accounts accessing com-
pany systems, cloud platforms, or sensitive data.
• Passwords must be a minimum of 12 characters and contain uppercase, lowercase,
numbers, and symbols.
• Password reuse across company systems is strictly prohibited.
• Service accounts must use API keys, certifcates, or tokens instead of static pass-
words.
• Shared accounts are prohibited except where explicitly approved by the Security
Team.
Password Management
• All employees must use an approved password manager (e.g., Bitwarden, 1Pass-
word).
• Default vendor passwords must be changed immediately upon deployment.
• Passwords must never be stored in plaintext, spreadsheets, or source code reposi-
tories.
• Temporary passwords (e.g., for new employees) must expire upon frst login.
Authentication Best Practices
• Enforce adaptive MFA (step-up authentication) for sensitive actions such as fnan-
cial transactions or accessing production systems.
• Single Sign-On (SSO) with centralized identity providers (Okta, Azure AD, or
Google Workspace) must be used for consistency.
